"{\"uid\": \"straitstimes.com-sport-snoop-dogg-stars-as-flame-sails-into-paris-for-olympics-opening-ceremony\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Choose edition  Search  singapore  asia  world  opinion  life  business  sport  Visual  Podcasts  SPH Rewards  STClassifieds  Paid press releases  Advertise with us  FAQs  Contact us  Sign up now:Get the biggest sports news in your inbox  US rapper Snoop Dogg holding the Olympic torch, on the day of the opening ceremony, in Saint-Denis, outside Paris.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 353, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 98, \"end\": 101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6708273155472848e-13, \"text\": \"SPH\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\"}, {\"begin\": 147, \"end\": 156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"score\": 0.9604822703099307, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Advertise\", \"types\": [\"Q7377\", \"Q729\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\"}, {\"begin\": 239, \"end\": 241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9997059191406686, \"rank\": 0.00022342123512926652, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 249, \"end\": 259, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Snoop Dogg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\"}, {\"begin\": 326, \"end\": 337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 0.9999532129581603, \"rank\": 3.2347179781335103e-05, \"text\": \"Saint-Denis\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}, {\"begin\": 347, \"end\": 352, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.817900550125576e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PHOTO: AFP  PublishedJul 27, 2024, 12:40 AM  UpdatedJul 27, 2024, 12:47 AM  PARIS - American rapper Snoop Dogg held the flame aloft as the Olympic torch relay neared the end of its 68-stage trek through France ahead of the July 26 opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 355, \"to\": 603, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 455, \"end\": 465, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Snoop Dogg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\"}, {\"begin\": 558, \"end\": 564, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999845886124, \"rank\": 1.5381400532252554e-08, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The flame was also borne by International Olympic Committee president Thomas Bach and a string of beaming, waving, volunteer carriers.\", \"from\": 605, \"to\": 739, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 633, \"end\": 664, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 675, \"end\": 686, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The relay is over,\\\" said an official preparing to drive away from the last stop on the Canal Saint Martin in a car carrying the slogan \\\"flame relay\\\".\", \"from\": 741, \"to\": 891, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Next stop: the cauldron.\\\"\", \"from\": 893, \"to\": 919, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The heavily-guarded flame was headed into the centre of town ready for the final lap of its long journey, ending with the revelation of which star would run the final leg and light the cauldron to officially start the Games.\", \"from\": 921, \"to\": 1145, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The last day of the relay was entitled the \\\"Epilogue\\\".\", \"from\": 1147, \"to\": 1201, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The torch had passed through some smarter Paris addresses, on July 14, the Bastille Day national holiday, and July 15, before circling the suburbs.\", \"from\": 1203, \"to\": 1350, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1245, \"end\": 1250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.817900550125576e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It started its final journey in Saint-Denis, home of the main Olympic Stadium and the Athletes' Village, on July 26, before sailing down the still-industrial Canal Saint-Denis and under the motorway that surrounds Paris into the traditionally blue-collar 19th-arrondissement, braving occasional drizzle.\", \"from\": 1352, \"to\": 1655, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1384, \"end\": 1395, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 0.9999532129581603, \"rank\": 3.2347179781335103e-05, \"text\": \"Saint-Denis\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}, {\"begin\": 1566, \"end\": 1571, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.817900550125576e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the Athletes' Village, Bach and former UN Secretary-General Ban Ki-moon took turns as torchbearers.\", \"from\": 1657, \"to\": 1759, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1683, \"end\": 1687, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"score\": 0.9999999999740794, \"rank\": 2.5898890368371294e-11, \"text\": \"Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\"}, {\"begin\": 1699, \"end\": 1719, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Secretary-General_of_the_United_Nations\", \"score\": 0.9999922983453046, \"rank\": 7.113398464146694e-06, \"text\": \"UN Secretary-General\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Secretary-General_of_the_United_Nations\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Secretary-General_of_the_United_Nations\"}, {\"begin\": 1720, \"end\": 1731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ban_Ki-moon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ban Ki-moon\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ban_Ki-moon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ban_Ki-moon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Now the real thing starts,\\\" Bach told a crowd of athletes.\", \"from\": 1761, \"to\": 1820, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1790, \"end\": 1794, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"score\": 0.9999999999740794, \"rank\": 2.5898890368371294e-11, \"text\": \"Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are all in sports.\", \"from\": 1821, \"to\": 1843, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We know that what happened until now is just training.\", \"from\": 1844, \"to\": 1898, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can feel the vibe among the athletes and the organisers.\\\"\", \"from\": 1899, \"to\": 1960, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Yiech Pur Biel, who ran the 800m for the Refugee Olympic Team at Rio in 2016 and is an IOC committee member representing South Sudan, found the experience moving.\", \"from\": 1962, \"to\": 2124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1972, \"end\": 1976, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lake_Biel\", \"score\": 0.9999992349974689, \"rank\": 7.650003520800966e-07, \"text\": \"Biel\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lake_Biel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lake_Biel\"}, {\"begin\": 2049, \"end\": 2052, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.478977683198567e-27, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You want me to cry, or what?\\\"\", \"from\": 2126, \"to\": 2156, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"he asked.\", \"from\": 2157, \"to\": 2166, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It is an honour to carry this torch for the first time.\\\"\", \"from\": 2167, \"to\": 2224, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am representing millions of refugees who are not here today, and also representing different athletes, different diversities and different communities, and that is what makes me so emotional to be here.\\\"\", \"from\": 2226, \"to\": 2432, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At the stadium, Snoop Dogg in a gold jacket before changing into his white relay tracksuit tried out his French.\", \"from\": 2434, \"to\": 2546, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2450, \"end\": 2460, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Snoop Dogg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\"}, {\"begin\": 2539, \"end\": 2545, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8722118520253134, \"rank\": 0.14651005371475861, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Vive les Jeux Olympiques,\\\" said the rapper, a special correspondent at the Games for US network NBC.\", \"from\": 2548, \"to\": 2649, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2634, \"end\": 2636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9997059191406686, \"rank\": 0.00022342123512926652, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2645, \"end\": 2648, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9999254982258927, \"rank\": 6.542827911724242e-05, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With the torch held aloft he danced, walked, ran and waved as the crowd shouted \\\"Snoop!\\\".\", \"from\": 2651, \"to\": 2740, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Imagine he's acting crazy, he takes the flame, he lights his joint with it!\\\"\", \"from\": 2742, \"to\": 2819, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"said one spectator, Toufik.\", \"from\": 2820, \"to\": 2847, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"From the stadium the flame crossed the canal in Aubervilliers for a series of boat rides, cruising past concrete factories and housing blocks to Paris accompanied by a crowd of spectators, security, officials and even canoeists in fancy dress.\", \"from\": 2849, \"to\": 3092, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2994, \"end\": 2999, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.817900550125576e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With each torch holding enough fuel for six minutes, progress was interrupted by frequent, choreographed, stops as one torch lit the next and cameras snapped and whirred.\", \"from\": 3094, \"to\": 3264, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It does not happen very often.\", \"from\": 3266, \"to\": 3297, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's exceptional,\\\" said Nathalie, who did not give her surname, from Aubervilliers as she stood on a bridge awaiting the flame.\", \"from\": 3298, \"to\": 3425, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The flame sailed under the peripherique and into Paris on a diesel-belching canal boat, the torch held aloft by its white-clad bearer to be greeted by a throng leaning over the rail on the next bridge.\", \"from\": 3427, \"to\": 3628, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3476, \"end\": 3481, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.817900550125576e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The relay toured the Parc de la Villette, turned into the Parc des Nations housing the 'clubhouses' of a string of countries, dominated by France in the Grande Halle, and including Brazil in a circus tent, and Mongolia in yurts.\", \"from\": 3630, \"to\": 3858, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3651, \"end\": 3670, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parc_de_la_Villette\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Parc de la Villette\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parc_de_la_Villette\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parc_de_la_Villette\"}, {\"begin\": 3769, \"end\": 3775, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999845886124, \"rank\": 1.5381400532252554e-08, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3811, \"end\": 3817, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\", \"score\": 0.8291061040763258, \"rank\": 0.20611657221181848, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\"}, {\"begin\": 3840, \"end\": 3848, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mongolia\", \"score\": 0.9999997762402267, \"rank\": 2.215004586194987e-07, \"text\": \"Mongolia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mongolia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mongolia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The relay then took to the water and cruised down the Canal de l'Ourcq, as the growing crowd roared and took up a football chant, towards the Canal Saint-Martin and its final encounter with the symbolic cauldron.\", \"from\": 3860, \"to\": 4072, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3914, \"end\": 3930, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canal_de_l'Ourcq\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Canal de l'Ourcq\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canal_de_l'Ourcq\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canal_de_l'Ourcq\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"AFP  Olympics  Olympics 2024  France  E-paper  Newsletters  Podcasts  RSS Feed  About Us  Terms & Conditions  Personal Data Protection Notice  Need help?\", \"from\": 4073, \"to\": 4226, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Reach us here.\", \"from\": 4227, \"to\": 4241, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertise with us\", \"from\": 4243, \"to\": 4260, \"entities\": []}]}"